==English==
[[Category:English words with multiple etymologies]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-bumble.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology 1===
Onomatopoeic. Confer ''[[bungle]]'', ''[[jumble]]'', ''[[fumble]]''.
====Noun====
'''bumble'''
#A [[confusion]], [[jumble]].

====Verb====
{{en-verb|bumble|bumbles|bumbled|bumbling}}
#To act in an [[inept]], [[clumsy]] or [[inexpert]] manner; to make [[mistakes]]. 
#:''Spiders build webs and wait for insects to '''bumble''' into them.''

===Etymology 2===
*Noun: From the verb.
*Verb: Frequentative of ''[[boom]]'' and/or ''[[bum]]''.
====Noun====
'''bumble'''
#A [[bumble-bee]].
#(''provincial'') The [[bittern]].

====Verb====
{{en-verb|bumble|bumbles|bumbled|bumbling}}
#{{intransitive}} To [[boom]], as a [[bittern]]; to [[buzz]], as a [[fly]].

